msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2010
msgid ""
"This feature's ``config.json`` setting is ``\"LdapServer\": \"\"`` with "
"string input."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2014
msgid "AD/LDAP Port"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2015
msgid ""
"The port Mattermost will use to connect to the AD/LDAP server. Defaults "
"to ``389``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2018
msgid ""
"This feature's ``config.json`` setting is ``\"LdapPort\": 389`` with "
"numerical input."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2023
msgid "The type of connection security Mattermost uses to connect to AD/LDAP."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2025
msgid ""
"**None**: No encryption, Mattermost will not attempt to establish an "
"encrypted connection to the AD/LDAP server."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2027
msgid ""
"**TLS**: Encrypts the communication between Mattermost and your server "
"using TLS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2029
msgid ""
"**STARTTLS**: Takes an existing insecure connection and attempts to "
"upgrade it to a secure connection using TLS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2031
msgid ""
"If the \"No encryption\" option is selected it is highly recommended that"
" the AD/LDAP connection is secured outside of Mattermost, for example, by"
" adding a stunnel proxy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2038
msgid "Skip Certificate Verification"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2039
msgid ""
"(Optional) The attribute in the AD/LDAP server that will be used to "
"populate the nickname of users in Mattermost."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2041
msgid ""
"**True**: Skips the certificate verification step for TLS or STARTTLS "
"connections. Not recommended for production environments where TLS is "
"required. For testing only."
