"start its search for users in the AD/LDAP tree."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2054
msgid ""
"This feature's ``config.json`` setting is ``\"BaseDN\": \"\"`` with "
"string input."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2058
msgid "Bind Username"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2059
msgid ""
"The username used to perform the AD/LDAP search. This should be an "
"account created specifically for use with Mattermost. Its permissions "
"should be limited to read-only access to the portion of the AD/LDAP tree "
"specified in the **Base DN** field. When using Active Directory, **Bind "
"Username** should specify domain in ``\"DOMAIN/username\"`` format. This "
"field is required, and anonymous bind is not currently supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2062
msgid ""
"This feature's ``config.json`` setting is ``\"BindUsername\": \"\"`` with"
" string input."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2066
msgid "Bind Password"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2067
msgid ""
"Password of the user given in **Bind Username**. Anonymous bind is not "
"currently supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2070
msgid ""
"This feature's ``config.json`` setting is ``\"BindPassword\": \"\"`` with"
" string input."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2074
msgid "User Filter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2075
msgid ""
"(Optional) Enter an AD/LDAP Filter to use when searching for user objects"
" (accepts `general syntax "
"<http://www.ldapexplorer.com/en/manual/109010000-ldap-filter-"
"syntax.htm>`__). Only the users selected by the query will be able to "
"access Mattermost."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2077
msgid "Sample filters for Active Directory:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2079
msgid ""
"To filter out disabled users: "
"``(&(objectCategory=Person)(!(UserAccountControl:1.2.840.113556.1.4.803:=2)))``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2080
msgid ""
"To filter out by group membership, determine the distinguishedName of "
"your group, then use the group membership general syntax format as your "
"filter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2082
msgid ""
"For example, if the security group distinguishedName is "
"``CN=group1,OU=groups,DC=example,DC=com``, then the user filter to use "
"is: ``(memberOf=CN=group1,OU=groups,DC=example,DC=com)``. Note that the "
"user must explicitly belong to this group for the filter to apply."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2084
msgid ""
"This filter uses the permissions of the **Bind Username** account to "
"execute the search. Administrators should make sure to use a specially "
"created account for Bind Username with read-only access to the portion of"
" the AD/LDAP tree specified in the **Base DN** field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2087
msgid ""
"This feature's ``config.json`` setting is ``\"UserFilter\": \"\"`` with "
"string input."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2091
msgid "Guest Filter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2094
msgid ""
"(Optional) Enter an AD/LDAP Filter to use when searching for external "
"users who have Guest Access to Mattermost. Only the users selected by the"
" query will be able to log in to and use Mattermost as Guests. This "
"filter default is blank."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2097
#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2463
msgid ""
"See the `Guest Accounts documentation "
"<https://docs.mattermost.com/deployment/guest-accounts.html>`__ for more "
"information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2100
msgid ""
"This feature's ``config.json`` setting is ``\"GuestFilter\": \"\"`` with "
"string input."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2104
msgid "Admin Filter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2107
msgid ""
"(Optional) Enter a filter to use for designating the System Admin role to"
" users. When enabled the user is promoted to this role on their next "
"login or at the next scheduled AD/LDAP sync. If the Admin Filter is "
"removed, users who are currently logged in retain their Admin role. When "
"they log out this is revoked and on their next login they will no longer "
"have Admin privileges."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2109
msgid ""
"This filter default is ``false`` and must be set to ``true`` in order for"
" the Admin Filter to be used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2112
msgid ""
"This feature's ``config.json`` setting is ``\"EnableAdminFilter\": "
"false`` with options ``true`` and ``false``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2116
msgid "Group Filter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2119
msgid ""
"(Optional) Enter an AD/LDAP Filter to use when searching for group "
"objects (accepts `general syntax "
"<http://www.ldapexplorer.com/en/manual/109010000-ldap-filter-"
"syntax.htm>`__). Only the groups selected by the query will be able to "
"access Mattermost."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2121
msgid ""
"This filter is defaulted to "
"``(|(objectClass=group)(objectClass=groupOfNames)(objectClass=groupOfUniqueNames))``"
" when blank."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2124
msgid ""
"This filter is used only when AD/LDAP Group Sync is enabled. See `AD/LDAP"
" Group Sync documentation <https://docs.mattermost.com/deployment/ldap-"
"group-sync.html>`_ for more information on enabling and configuring "
"AD/LDAP Group Sync."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2127
msgid ""
"This feature's ``config.json`` setting is ``\"GroupFilter\": \"\"`` with "
"string input."
msgstr ""

