msgid ""
"The attribute in the AD/LDAP server used to populate the email address "
"field in Mattermost."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2188
msgid ""
"Email notifications will be sent to this email address, and this email "
"address may be viewable by other Mattermost users depending on privacy "
"settings chosen by the System Admin."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2191
#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2438
msgid ""
"This feature's ``config.json`` setting is ``\"EmailAttribute\": \"\"`` "
"with string input."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2195
#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2442
msgid "Username Attribute"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2196
msgid ""
"The attribute in the AD/LDAP server used to populate the username field "
"in Mattermost. This may be the same as the Login ID Attribute."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2198
msgid ""
"This attribute will be used within the Mattermost user interface to "
"identify and mention users. For example, if a Username Attribute is set "
"to **john.smith** a user typing ``@john`` will see ``@john.smith`` in "
"their auto-complete options and posting a message with ``@john.smith`` "
"will send a notification to that user that they've been mentioned."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2200
msgid ""
"The **Username Attribute** may be set to the same value used to sign-in "
"to the system, called a **Login ID Attribute**, or it can be mapped to a "
"different value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2203
#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2446
msgid ""
"This feature's ``config.json`` setting is ``\"UsernameAttribute\": \"\"``"
" with string input."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2207
msgid "ID Attribute"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2208
msgid ""
"The attribute in the AD/LDAP server used as a unique identifier in "
"Mattermost. It should be an AD/LDAP attribute with a value that does not "
"change."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2210
msgid ""
"If a user's ID Attribute changes, a new Mattermost account (unassociated "
"with the previous one) is created. To prevent this, it's recommended that"
" a unique attribute such as ``objectGUID`` in Active Directory and "
"``entryUUID`` in LDAP be used instead. Before making any changes confirm "
"with your LDAP provider whether these attributes are available in your "
"environment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2213
msgid ""
"If you need to change this field after users have already logged in, use "
"the `mattermost ldap idmigrate <https://about.mattermost.com/default-"
"platform-ldap-idmigrate>`__ CLI tool."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2216
#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2454
