"Normally this attribute is the same as the \"Username Attribute\" field "
"above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2223
msgid ""
"If your team typically uses domain\\username to log in to other services "
"with AD/LDAP, you may enter domain\\username in this field to maintain "
"consistency between sites."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2226
msgid ""
"This feature's ``config.json`` setting is ``\"LoginIdAttribute\": \"\"`` "
"with string input."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2230
msgid "Login Field Name"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2231
msgid ""
"The placeholder text that appears in the login field on the login page. "
"Typically this would be whatever name is used to refer to AD/LDAP "
"credentials in your company, so it is recognizable to your users. "
"Defaults to **AD/LDAP Username**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2234
msgid ""
"This feature's ``config.json`` setting is ``\"LoginFieldName\": \"\"`` "
"with string input."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2238
msgid "Synchronization Interval (minutes)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2239
msgid ""
"Set how often Mattermost accounts synchronize attributes with AD/LDAP, in"
" minutes. When synchronizing, Mattermost queries AD/LDAP for relevant "
"account information and updates Mattermost accounts based on changes to "
"attributes (first name, last name, and nickname). When accounts are "
"disabled in AD/LDAP users are made inactive in Mattermost, and their "
"active sessions are revoked once Mattermost synchronizes attributes. To "
"synchronize immediately after disabling an account, use the \"AD/LDAP "
"Synchronize Now\" button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2242
msgid ""
"This feature's ``config.json`` setting is ``\"SyncIntervalMinutes\": 60``"
" with numerical input."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2246
msgid "Maximum Page Size"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2247
msgid ""
"The maximum number of users the Mattermost server will request from the "
"AD/LDAP server at one time. Use this setting if your AD/LDAP server "
"limits the number of users that can be requested at once."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2249
msgid "A value of 0 is unlimited and does not paginate the results."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2250
msgid ""
"A value of 1500 is recommended to align with the default AD/LDAP "
"``MaxPageSize`` setting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2253
msgid ""
"This feature's ``config.json`` setting is ``\"MaxPageSize\": 0`` with "
"numerical input."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2257
msgid "Query Timeout (seconds)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/config-settings.rst:2258
msgid ""
